<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-10-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-10-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="1116" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1116">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to <persName type="to">Ali Ferrouh Bey</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-10-11"><hi rend="italic">October 11,
                                1898</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 11.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Acknowledging your note of the 11th
                            instant, in which you reply to mine of this date, relative to the
                            refusal of the Turkish consul at New York to visé the passport of the
                            Rev. S. L. Beiler, for use in traveling through Palestine, and inform me
                            that the consul has been directed by wire to visé the passport, I have
                            the honor to thank you for your very prompt and courteous attention to
                            the matter.</p>
                        <p>Be pleased to accept, etc.,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>